  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The plan of draining the flood\nwaters of Union Park by the means\nof large drainage cisterns built into\nihe gravel will be tried. The city\ncouncil last night ordered the board\nof public works to proceed with the\nwork of installing the necessary\ndrain wells.\n\n\nThis idea was advanced by the\nUnion Park Improvement club and\nran be installed for few thousand\ndollars, as against the plan of City\nEngineer Ralston for a surface\ndrainage sewer to cost $150.000.\nThe city council has set aside $500\nTO care for the surface water.\n\n\nSpokane Press, 3Oc a Month."
    }
